@node "BRIEF" "Brief Description of Pictures"
@next "TIFF"
@prev "MAIN"

This is a collection of Photographs of the World of Amiga show 1997 which
have been scanned and placed on Aminet.  

The Pictures are as follows:

@{b}AISTAND.TIFF@{ub}   Is a picture of the Amiga International Stand.
                       It is @{i}702204@{ui} bytes in size.

@{b}AMFORMAT.TIFF@{ub}  Is a picture of the Amiga Format Stand.
                       It is @{i}692808@{ui} bytes in size.

@{b}DIGITA.TIFF@{ub}    Is a picture of the Digita Stand.
                       It is @{i}703959@{ui} bytes in size.

@{b}HIQ.TIFF@{ub}       Is a picture of a computer running the Siamese System
                       It is @{i}698748@{ui} bytes in size.

@{b}MICRONIK.TIFF@{ub}  Is a picture of a Micronik Tower system.
                       It is @{i}696372@{ui} bytes in size.

@{b}PLEASENCE.TIFF@{ub} Is a picture of David near the Power Computing Stand.
                       It is @{i}699804@{ui} bytes in size.
                       My apologies if I have spelt his surname incorrectly.
@endnode
@node "TIFF" "Viewing the Pictures"
@next "AUTHOR"
@prev "BRIEF"

All of these Pictures are in a TIFF format.  I tried viewing them with
ViewTek, but they seemed distorted.  I have included some TIFF Datatypes
(Sorry, I don't know who the author is) in the "TIFF Datatypes" Directory -
it contains the following files:

@{b}TIFF@{ub}          Should be placed in Devs:Datatypes @{i}174@{ui} bytes.
@{b}TIFF.datatype@{ub} Should be placed in Classes:Datatypes @{i}22916@{ui} bytes.

You should then be able to view the pictures using Multiview.

If this fails, I would advise you to use TIFFView by Bert Wynants.  On
Aminet, this can be found as:

gfx/show
TIFFView116.lha
TIFFView117pch.lha
@endnode
